text: Anne Margrethe Larsen Anne Margrethe Larsen (born 28 May 1950, in Haugesund, Rogaland) is a Norwegian politician representing the Liberal Party. She is currently a representative of Vest-Agder in the Storting and was first elected in 2005. ==Storting committees== * 2005-2009 member of the Foreign Affairs committee. * 2005-2009 member of the Extended Foreign Affairs committee. * 2005-2009 reserve member of the Electoral committee. ==External links== * * Venstre.no Category:1950 births Category:Living people Category:Liberal Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:Women members of the Storting Category:21st-century Norwegian politicians Category:21st- century Norwegian women politicians
